If I can guess optimised approach (greedy) means leaving less fragmentation when we book the room.

If [s,e] is being inserted between `[s1,e1] < [s,e] > [s2,e2]` so wasted time would be `e1-s + e - s2` which we'll have to minimize.


```java

Integer scheduleMeeting(startTime, endTime) {
     int roomID = -1;
     int leastWastage = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
     for (int i = 0; i < rooms.length; i++) {
             int wastage = calculateWastage(room[i], start, end);
             if (wastage != -1 && wastage < leastWastage) {
                        leastWastage = wastage;
                        roomID = i;
             }
    }
    if (roomId == -1) { return -1; }
    book(roomId, start, end);
    return roomId;
}

